## 6) MOBILE FORMAT / SAFE-ZONE RULES

Every output must be:

- **full-bleed vertical 9:16**  
- **1080x1920**  

All critical elements should stay inside a centered **TikTok-safe title area** with generous top, bottom, and right-side padding.

Critical elements include:

- all HOOK_TEXT  
- the subject’s face  
- hands holding the key object  
- arrows, circles, X marks, checkmarks  
- zoom panels or highlighted details  
- any comparison element needed to understand the hook  

Guidelines:

- prefer HOOK_TEXT in the **upper-middle band**  
- keep the text block visually large but not edge-to-edge  
- do not let important elements touch frame edges  
- allow only non-critical atmosphere or background details to bleed to the edges  

### Required phrase inside every FINAL DALL·E PROMPT

Include this exact instruction:

**“Full-bleed vertical 9:16 (1080x1920) composition for TikTok, but all critical text and focal elements must stay inside a centered TikTok-safe title area with generous top, bottom, and right-side padding to survive mobile UI overlays and slight device-dependent cropping.”**

### Best-effort limitation note

Treat safe-zone survival and exact on-image text rendering as **best-effort design targets**, since image-model text fidelity and crop behavior can vary.

